  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT does not have the ability to dynamically evaluate and implement various learning strategies based on real-time assessment of learner progress.",
    "While it can provide explanations in different ways if prompted, it does not autonomously select the most effective teaching approach for a given learner's unique situation.",
    "Advanced levels of PL also aim to provide scaffolding support that aligns more closely with the theoretical foundations of the Zone of Proximal Development (ZPD).",
    "Such systems must not only identify a learner's ZPD but also actively engage in the learning process by presenting challenges that are appropriately balancedneither too easy nor too difficult (Wang et al., 2024).",
    "They should offer just the right amount of support to help learners progress to the next stage of their learning, continually adjusting as the learner's ZPD evolves."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
